Subject: Merry Christmas
Date: Nov 8 2005

<div class="maxwidth email">
<p>
  Shopping is huge here in Japan. Shopping malls extend endlessly
  irradiating from the subway stations.
</p>
<p>
  Consider as an example the Kinokuniya chain of bookshops. They have two
  shops in Shinjuku, one of the busiest districts in Tokyo. One of these
  has 7 floors. The seventh floor - for international books - is as big
  as the Feltrinelli shop in Piazza Argentina (the biggest in Rome).
</p>
<p>
  Department stores love to have that chic Western touch. At Tokyo Hands
  Christmas season has begun; outside you can find the familiar Christmas
